      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix stale Discord ACP binding recovery",
        "body": "## Summary\n- ignore Discord ACP session bindings when ACP/ACP dispatch/acpx is disabled so stale ACP routes cannot override the configured native Discord route\n- unbind recoverable ACP conversation bindings when acpx exits with code 1 and show a more actionable next step instead of the generic ACP_TURN_FAILED retry hint\n- add ACPX launch/child-exit diagnostics with lease id, command hash, cwd, PID, exit code/signal, and stderr log path without logging secrets\n\n## Root cause\nDiscord conversation bindings treated ACP session keys as explicit focus bindings forever. After ACP/acpx was disabled, stale ACP bindings and stale open process leases survived from earlier runs, so Discord could continue routing turns through an ACP session even though the live gateway was configured for native Codex and no acpx plugin was loaded. The resulting recoverable acpx code-1 failures were surfaced as repeated generic ACP_TURN_FAILED messages instead of clearing the stale binding.\n\n## Tests\n- pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-discord.config.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/route-resolution.test.ts\n- env -u CODEX_HOME pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-acpx.config.ts extensions/acpx/src/codex-auth-bridge.test.ts extensions/acpx/src/runtime.test.ts extensions/acpx/src/process-lease.test.ts\n- pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit.config.ts packages/acp-core/src/runtime/error-text.test.ts\n- pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.auto-reply-reply.config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-acp.test.ts\n\nDo not merge until verified against a live Discord turn on the affected deployment.",
